  "text": "Studies have been reported on the antimicrobial effect of green tea catechins and black tea theaflavins on virtual cell membranes with the aid of computer modeling [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the present study, the Langmuir monolayers composed of bacterial phospholipids were used as model membranes to study interactions of the five naturally occurring phenolic compounds (Figure 1 ) 2,5-dihydroxybenzaldehyde, 2-hydroxy-5-methoxybenzaldehyde, and the plant essential oil compounds carvacrol, cinnamaldehyde, and geraniol, previously found to be active against both Gram-positive and Gram-negative pathogenic microorganisms. ",
